	(1748, 51, 0, 'Production Dept. Meeting MINUTES - June 14, 2022 ', 'production-dept-meeting-minutes-june-14-2022', '<h1 style="text-align: right;">Production Dept. Meeting MINUTES <br />- June&nbsp; 14, 2022</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Participants:</strong> Benjamin Trenkle (Department Coordinator), David Jardin (Team Leader), Hannes Papenberg (Team Leader), Harald Leithner (Release Lead 5.0), Christiane Maier-Stadtherr (Team Leader), Viviana Menzel (Assistant Team Leader), Sigrid Gramlinger (Team Leader), Shivam Rajput (Team Leader), Philip Walton (Marketing Liaison), Robert Deutz (Team Leader) <br /> <strong>Absent:</strong> Mike Brandner (Team Leader), Roland Dalmulder (Release Lead 4.2), Franciska Perisa (Release Lead 4.2), Llewellyn van der Merwe (Assistant Department Coordinator), Jacob Waisner (Team Leader), Niels Braczek (Team Leader), Tobias Zulauf (Release Lead 3.10)</p>\r\n<h3><a href="/departments/production">Production Department</a> Coordinator (Benjamin Trenkle)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Budget Deadline Tomorrow</li>\r\n<li>Goals deadline end of month</li>\r\n<li>Please check volunteers team profile</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Joomla! <a href="/teams/joomla-enhancement-development-team">Enhancement Development</a> Team (Shivam Rajput)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Google Summer of Code (GSoC)\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Coding Period Kicked off</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Summer of Code (SoC)\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>For this year we haven\'t selected any student for the project. We did not have a good pool of students.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/security-strike-team">Security Strike</a> Team (David Jardin)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Successful TUF sprint in Nürnberg, Germany. Server Side toolchain was improved, multiple upstream PRs for the TUF client were created and the implementation in the CMS was continued to a point where update information is now fetched, verified and stored. Important outcome was that we can’t implement a “core-only” solution as a first step - we have to build the j.org repo with 3rd party extensions in mind and that will also affect the implementation in the CMS. A Follow-up sprint is planned.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/automated-tests-working-group">Automated Testing</a> Team (Hannes Papenberg)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Working on moving our system tests to cypress.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Releaseleads (Harald, Niels, Roland, Franciska, Benjamin, George, Tobias, Llewellyn)</h3>\r\n<h4>* Release Lead 4.1 (Benjamin Trenkle)</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Last 4.1.x will be released on the 21st of June. Thanks for all the help..</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>* Release lead 3.10 (Tobias Zulauf):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Joomla 3.10.10-rc1 has been published</li>\r\n<li>Joomla 3.10.10 will be published on the 21.06.2022</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/cms-release-team">CMS Release</a> Team (Sigrid Gramlinger)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We started testing RC packages of 4.1.5 and 3.10.10 and right after the releases we will focus all testing on 4.2.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/cms-maintenance-team">CMS Maintenance</a> Team (Robert Deutz)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Team lead election is on the way</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 1434, 1, 1755, '2022-06-22 10:35:32', 0, '2022-06-22 10:38:05', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1749, 55, 0, 'Operations Department Meeting Minutes - 2022-05-03', 'operations-department-meeting-minutes-2022-05-03', '<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Participants: </span><span style="caret-color: auto; font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Harald Leithner (Director), Jaz Parkyn (JED TL), Olaf Offick (Forum TL)</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-9f563630-7fff-492e-7980-180fc82479d3"></span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Apologies:&nbsp; </span><span style="caret-color: auto; font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Sander Potjer (JVP TL), Luca Marzo (JCM ATL), Roland Dalmulder (JVP ATL), Sebastien Lapoux (Showcase TL), Toivo Talikka (Forum ATL), Claire Mandville (TL)</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<br /><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Department Coordinator:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px; white-space: pre-wrap;">Migration from 1Password to Vaultwarden completed</span></span></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px; white-space: pre-wrap;">Joomla.org Template makes small steps</span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Extensions Directory team:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Team meeting was on 29th April, followed by JED4 development meeting on 1st May, minutes available shortly.</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">An item will be added to the listing checklist to give further definition on how extensions reported for not being J4 compatible when the J4 compatible flag has been checked will be handled</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">Further work is being done on J4 checks for the JED Checker</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">JED4 updates:</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">New structures for Extensions and reviews have been implemented and support coding is underway.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">New code to auto-migrate JED3 data to JED4 written and tested.</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">Previously created views are now being hooked up to the database</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">We hope to merge all WIP branches together shortly, before deploying to a staging server</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Forum team:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px; white-space: pre-wrap;">Testing sandbox version for cloudflare compatibility </span></span></li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, 1435, 1, 547, '2022-06-23 15:18:57', 0, '2022-06-23 15:20:42', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1750, 55, 0, 'Operations Department Meeting Minutes - 2022-05-31', 'operations-department-meeting-minutes-2022-05-31', '<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Participants: </span><span style="caret-color: auto; font-size: 14.6667px; white-space: pre-wrap;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;">Harald Leithner (Director), Llewellyn van der Merwe (Assistant) , Olaf Offick (Forum TL), Sander Potjer (JVP TL)</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Apologies:&nbsp; </span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Roland Dalmulder (JVP ATL), , Sebastien Lapoux (Showcase TL), Toivo Talikka (Forum ATL), Luca Marzo (JCM ATL), Jaz Parkyn (JED TL)</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Roboto,sans-serif; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Department Coordinator:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="color: #000000; font-family: Roboto, sans-serif;"><span style="font-size: 13.3333px; white-space: pre-wrap;">The prize of the 20i.com FOSS AWARDS 2022 is a 6 Core VPS which we got today. We will use it as part of our