transparent; font-size: 11.5pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> drop down into one dropdown i.e </span><span style="font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-size: 11.5pt; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Interactive Tour</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; font-size: 11.5pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">.</span></li>\r\n<li>Added form fields in the tour step for an interactive tour.</li>\r\n<li>Changed value for interactive step field in <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">extensions.sql</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">.</span></li>\r\n<li>Added a new dropdown field which would be visible after selecting Interactive tour.</li>\r\n<li>Created Interactive Tour dropdown, and in that, there will be three sub-fields i.e <span style="font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-size: 11.5pt; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Button,</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; font-size: 11.5pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> </span><span style="font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-size: 11.5pt; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Form Field</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; font-size: 11.5pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> and </span><span style="font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-size: 11.5pt; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Others</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; font-size: 11.5pt; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">.</span></li>\r\n<li>Solved the major problem for the interactive step and made the <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">+New Button</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> Work.</span></li>\r\n<li>Implemented the functionality, If the user selects the <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Button</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> field then the user will be able to click the </span><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">+New button</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> in spite of clicking on the </span><span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Next Button</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> in the pop-up.</span></li>\r\n<li>Worked on the feature and while selecting the <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Button</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> field the Next Button won\'t be visible.</span></li>\r\n<li>Implemented the feature and now If the user selects the <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Text field</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> then it will disable the Next Button until someone enters any value in the field.</span></li>\r\n<li>Added EventListner <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Click</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> on the target of the step for the Button field in Interactive Tour.</span></li>\r\n<li>Added EventListner <span style="font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">input</span><span style="color: #121212; font-family: Arial; font-size: 11.5pt; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> on the target of the step for Form Field.</span></li>\r\n<li>Done changes for default tours in <span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">extensions.sql</span><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> for changing the value according to Interactive tour.</span></li>\r\n<li>Code formatting.</li>\r\n<li>Added one more field in the <span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Interactive step</span><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> for default values.</span></li>\r\n<li>Added logic in javascript for incorporating changes for adding one more field in the <span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Interactive step</span><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">.</span></li>\r\n<li>Made changes in default tours in <span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">extensions.sql</span><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> to make it compatible with interactive tours.</span></li>\r\n<li>Identified and solved the problem and made two consecutive mandatory fields `Next Button` enable/disable in the <span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #be3933; background-color: #fff7f5; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">interactive step</span><span style="font-size: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> work.</span></li>\r\n<li>Tested the changes done for all the default tours to ensure all the tours are working with interaction.</li>\r\n<li>Did the changes in Default tours and made improvements in interactive tours.</li>\r\n<li>Prioritized the task for next week.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Pull Request:</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> </span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/16">https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/16</a><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/16"></a></span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/16"></a></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/11"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/11</span></a></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-ce9d27c2-7fff-db23-9c21-dacb472902e3"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #121212; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><a href="https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/4"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #1155cc; background-color: transparent; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; text-decoration-line: underline; text-decoration-skip-ink: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">https://github.com/joomla-projects/gsoc22_guided-tour/pull/1</span></a></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 1516, 3, 7131, '2022-11-20 21:29:14', 7131, '2022-11-21 14:47:49', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1831, 51, 0, 'Production Dept. Meeting MINUTES - November 15, 2022', 'production-dept-meeting-minutes-november-15-2022', '<h1 style="text-align: right;">Production Dept. Meeting MINUTES <br />- November&nbsp; 15, 2022</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Participants:</strong> Benjamin Trenkle (Department Coordinator), Hannes Papenberg (Team Leader), Harald Leithner (Release Lead 5.0), Mike Brandner (Team Leader), Olivier Buisard (Release Manager 4.3), Shirielle “SD” Williams (Release Manager 4.3), Franciska Perisa (Release Lead 4.2), Christiane Maier-Stadtherr (Team Leader), Crystal Dionysopoulos (Team Leader), Llewellyn van der Merwe (Assistant Department Coordinator), Jacob Waisner (Team Leader), Niels Braczek (Team Leader), Sigrid Gramlinger (Team Leader), Shivam Rajput (Team Leader), Philip Walton (Marketing Liaison), Robert Deutz (Team Leader), Tobias Zulauf (Release Lead 3.10) <br /> <strong>Absent:</strong> Viviana Menzel (Assistant Team Leader), David Jardin (Team Leader), Roland Dalmulder (Release Lead 4.2)</p>\r\n<h3><a href="/departments/production">Production Department</a> Coordinator (Benjamin Trenkle)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If someone is interested in joining leadership event <a href="https://23.foss-backstage.de">https://23.foss-backstage.de</a> team leads can get a free digital ticket. We also have the budget for 4 local tickets (including hotel + travel). If someone is interested, please send an application to Benjamin Trenkle</li>\r\n<li>The future strategy of Joomla includes creating awareness (we\'re still out there). If you find an interesting event and think someone from Joomla should be a participant, also get in touch with Benjamin Trenkle</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/bug-squad">Bug Squad</a> Team (Jacob Waisner)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>704 Issues open</li>\r\n<li>Nicola Galgano organised a small PBF last saturday. It reduced our open issues from 767 to currently 703.</li>\r\n<li>Thanks to Nicola for scheduling another bug sprint for this coming weekend.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Joomla! <a href="/teams/joomla-enhancement-development-team">Enhancement Development</a> Team (Shivam Rajput)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Google Summer of Code (GSoC)\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We are final evaluation for the last 2 projects of GSoC 2022.</li>\r\n<li>GSoC 2023 schedule is announced.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We are already receiving responses from the students for GSoC 2023.\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>GSoC 2023 open for org applications January 23 - February 7</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Timeline\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href="https://developers.google.com/open-source/gsoc/timeline">https://developers.google.com/open-source/gsoc/timeline</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Joomla! <a href="/teams/accessibility-team">Accessibility</a> Team (Christiane Maier-Stadtherr, Viviana Menzel)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>JSearching in VET for a technical writer for docs (Thanks, Crystal)</li>\r\n<li>Accessibility Plugin - see Viviana’s post on mattermost (<a href="https://joomlacommunity.cloud.mattermost.com/main/pl/ewcg3fph3jdrbp3e9itexk4djw">https://joomlacommunity.cloud.mattermost.com/main/pl/ewcg3fph3jdrbp3e9itexk4djw</a>)</li>\r\n<li>Follow up discussion about spaces / tabs in PSR-12:<br /> <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/discussions/38408">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/discussions/38408</a><br /> <a href="departments/production/reports/1802-production-dept-meeting-minutes-septemeber-06-2022">https://volunteers.joomla.org/departments/production/reports/1802-production-dept-meeting-minutes-septemeber-06-2022</a><br /> <a href="https://github.com/php-fig/per-coding-style/issues/25">https://github.com/php-fig/per-coding-style/issues/25</a><br /> Robert will contact PHP-FIG</li>\r\n<li>Angie Radtke did some investigation on an installation progress bar and will write about it on the JCM. A good example how things are not as easy.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Joomla! <a href="/teams/joomla-experience-team">Experience</a> Team (Crystal Dionysopoulos)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>JXT would like closer collaboration with other teams making feature decisions in future releases, how can we best accomplish that?\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Crystal will create a board in the PLT channel for team leads to collaborate on overarching goals and strategy for the CMS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Welcome Yuusuf to the JXT! He is joining us as a UX writer.</li>\r\n<li>We have two potential new members coming from outside of the Joomla community - one content designer early in his career, and an established UX researcher/strategist.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/cms-release-team">CMS Release</a> Team (Sigrid Gramlinger)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Internal documentation on building releases was updated/restructured by Harald and also integrated from Docs by Franciska. Thanks!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/cms-maintenance-team">CMS Maintenance</a> Team (Robert Deutz)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We are again back at well over 200 (216 to be exact) open PRs. What is our plan to lower this number?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/automated-tests-working-group">Automated Testing</a> Team (Hannes Papenberg)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>How should we handle broken/non-existent error handling? Ex.:<br /> <a href="https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/39059">https://github.com/joomla/joomla-cms/pull/39059</a></li>\r\n<li>Working on improving CD setup for search and weblinks, but currently this is WIP.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Release Managers (Harald, Niels, Olivier, SD, Roland, Franciska, Tobias, Llewellyn)</h3>\r\n<h4>Release Lead 5.0 (Harald Leithner, Niels Braczek):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Are we going to remove UCM from 5.0?\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>No</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Release Lead 4.3 (Olivier Buisard, Shirielle “SD” Williams):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>For the upcoming builds on Nov 29 and Dec 27, the current plan is to invite Phil, Benjamin, and Sigrid, is there anyone else who would like to be invited? We understand due to time differences it may be a challenge.</li>\r\n<li>Continuing our dry-run in preparation for the pre-build on Nov 19th. A reminder will be sent Nov 18th which will include what can be tested.</li>\r\n<li>An article for the magazine will include at a high-level what might be included in the release along with a call for help</li>\r\n<li>Even though we are only going for alpha, can we please push changes like tags through before this happens?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Release Lead 4.2 (Roland Dalmulder, Franciska Perisa):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Next release (4.2.6) is one week earlier as planned: December 13 instead of 20 to avoid Christmas holidays</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Maintainer Framework (Niels Braczek):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Unfortunately behind schedule with version 3 of the framework. May pick up speed again soon.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Maintainer Docker (Llewellyn van der Merwe):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Updated all images to Joomla 4.2.5</li>\r\n<li>Added PHP 8.0 images to Joomla 3.10</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/software-architecture-strategy-working-group">Software Architecture &amp; Strategy</a> Team (Niels Braczek)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Send out motions about:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Entrance Vote for "Decoupling Output"</p>\r\n<p>Proposed Feature: "Decouple the output layer from the core of the CMS so that necessary changes to the CMS code require as few changes as possible to the templates and their overrides."<br />See <a href="https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/36">https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/36</a> for more details.</p>\r\n<p>This feature is eligible for the Core.<br /> A working group will be formed to work out the implementation details through the RFC process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Entrance Vote for "Append Form"</p>\r\n<p>Proposed Feature: "Add the possibility to append any form to an article. This could be a comment form, a buy button or a lead/contact form."<br /> See <a href="https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/18">https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/18</a> for more Details.</p>\r\n<p>This feature is eligible for the Core.<br /> A working group will be formed to work out the implementation details through the RFC process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Entrance Vote for "Form Admin"</p>\r\n<p>Proposed Feature: "A form editor to allow modifying forms, to add or remove predefined fields and custom fields and change their order."<br /> See <a href="https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/31">https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/31</a> for more Details.</p>\r\n<p>This feature is eligible for the Core.<br /> A working group will be formed to work out the implementation details through the RFC process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p>Entrance Vote for "Simple CCK"</p>\r\n<p>Proposed Feature: "A \'Simple CCK\' system to extend the article data model with the help of custom fields and the necessary functions to filter the contents according to any criteria and to display them in a specific sorting order."<br /> See <a href="https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/26">https://github.com/joomla/rfc/pull/26</a> for more Details.</p>\r\n<p>This feature is eligible for the Core.<br /> A working group will be formed to work out the implementation details through the RFC process.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>We are talking to some candidates to strengthen the team. First results are hoped for at the next meeting.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Other Business</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Planned usage of playbooks and boards in Mattermost? (Is there a plan or recommendation?)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 1517, 2, 1755, '2022-11-22 20:23:07', 1755, '2022-11-22 20:33:08', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1832, 55, 0, 'Operations Department Meeting Minutes - 2022-11-15', 'operations-department-meeting-minutes-2022-11-15', '<p><strong>Participants:</strong> Harald Leithner (Director), Llewellyn van der Merwe (DC Assistant), Mark Fleeson (JED TL), Olaf Offick (Forum TL), Luca Marzo (JCM ATL &amp; TL ATL &amp; P ATL), Sander Potjer (JVP TL), Roland Dalmulder (JVP ATL), Claire Mandville (TL TL) <br /> <strong>Absent:</strong> Sebastien Lapoux (Showcase TL), Toivo Talikka (Forum ATL), Soren Jensen (Capital TL), Donata Kalnenaite (Privacy TL)</p>\r\n<h3>Motions:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Proposed merging (Show Case, Volunteers, Webmaster) into Community Site Team</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Department Coordinator:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Welcome Mark Fleeson as new JED Team Lead</li>\r\n<li>Welcome to Mattermost\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The transition worked really great, most of the communication moved to mattermost within one week.</li>\r\n<li>The announcement wasn’t optimal but it wasn’t too bad</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Talking about the future of the Operation Department\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Teams which are not responding\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Privacy Compliance Team is not responding</li>\r\n<li>Show Case Team is not responding</li>\r\n<li>Volunteers Portal Team is not responding</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Operations Team Leads which are withdrawn from Joomla!\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sander Potjer (Stepped down)</li>\r\n<li>Soren Jensen - did a break for personal reason (never seen in operations)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Operations Team Leads which are not responding\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Sebastien Lapoux (Not seen in operations since February 2022)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Teams with less than 3 members\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Capital Team</li>\r\n<li>Trademark Team - Asking for volunteers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Website updates\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We need a plan for our properties to upgrade, it doesn’t look too good for a new template in time.</li>\r\n<li>Joomla 4 Update</li>\r\n<li>Status Forum Software and Cloudflare?\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Not done yet, hopefully by the end of the year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Docs.Joomla.org? Status</li>\r\n<li>Manual.joomla.org - We use docusaurus with renovate bot which Semi automatically (creates a pull request) updates the github repository. Drone does Autodeploy on PR merge.</li>\r\n<li>internal.joomla.org - We use docusaurus with renovate bot which Semi automatically (creates a pull request) updates the github repository. Drone does Autodeploy on PR merge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Single sign on for more (all) websites\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Developer.joomla.org - should be easy</li>\r\n<li>Joomla.org - should be easy</li>\r\n<li>joomla.org/3</li>\r\n<li>Certification.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Magazine.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Community.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Extensions.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Identity.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Appsserver.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Showcase.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>tm.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Volunteers.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>forum.joomla.org</li>\r\n<li>Opensourcematters.org</li>\r\n<li>joomlafoundation.org</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Capital team:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Capital Team has 2 active* members, but no team leader:<br /> (Joe, Llewellyn)</li>\r\n<li>We need a team leader and more members urgently</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Extensions Directory team:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Extensions Team has 6 active members, Denes, Oh and Jeroen (Tickets), Denis (JedChecker), Mark (JED 4 and TL), Claire (VEL and trademark), Jaz (Adviser)</li>\r\n<li>Mark is presenting to the Joomla Extension Developer JUG on Thursday 17th attempting to get extra helpers for the JED team.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Forum team:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Forum Team has 5 active members (Global Moderators/Admins):<br /> (Olaf, Toivo, Peter, MIG, Per)</li>\r\n<li>Forum upgrade - Not done yet, hopefully by the end of the year</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Trademark &amp; Licensing team:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Current Team is Mandville &amp; Luca.</li>\r\n<li>Several reports dealt with by contacting domain and registrar with no positive outcomes. Mainly due to GDPR restrictions and cost of chasing domains through udrp.</li>\r\n<li>Trademark checker group on mattermost - liaison from Showcase/Resources required to join</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Volunteers Portal team:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>No response on the call for a new team lead. Sander will step down by the end of November 2022 completely (and other teams like Webmaster/operations). Please make sure the access to Vault, Rochen tickets, Portals etc.. will be removed.</li>\r\n<li>Roland has keys/knowledge of the current setup.</li>\r\n<li>Team does no longer comply with the OSM-bylaws once Sander stepped down, so possibly the team needs to be merged or responsibility of the portal to be moved to another team.</li>\r\n<li>Anything needed from Sander\'s side before stepping down?</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 1518, 1, 1755, '2022-11-23 09:31:08', 0, '2022-11-23 09:36:13', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1833, 0, 177, 'GSOC 2022 - Schema.org | Week 10', 'gsoc-2022-schema-org-week-10', '<p><strong>Date:</strong> 22nd August – 28th August</p>\r\n<p>Hi, this is the progress report for the Schema.org project which is currently part of GSoC 2022.</p>\r\n<p>Tasks completed this week:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>normalizeDurationsToISO(): To normalize duration to ISO duration format</li>\r\n<li>convertToArray(): To convert repeatable fields into an array</li>\r\n<li>Storing filtered and unfiltered schema in database</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, 1519, 5, 7190, '2022-08-29 09:26:48', 7190, '2022-11-24 09:56:12', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1834, 0, 177, 'GSOC 2022 - Schema.org | Week 16', 'gsoc-2022-schema-org-week-16', '<p><strong>Date:</strong> 3rd October – 8th October</p>\r\n<p>Hi, this is the progress report for the Schema.org project which is currently part of GSoC 2022.</p>\r\n<p>Tasks completed this week:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Added Subscriber Interface in Recipe and Blog plugins</li>\r\n<li>Updated validation in storeSchemaToStandardLocation()</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, 1520, 2, 7190, '2022-10-09 05:54:53', 7190, '2022-11-24 09:56:50', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1835, 0, 177, 'GSOC 2022 - Schema.org | Week 20', 'gsoc-2022-schema-org-week-20', '<p><strong>Date:</strong> 31st October – 6th November</p>\r\n<p>Hi, this is the progress report for the Schema.org project which is currently part of GSoC 2022.</p>\r\n<p>Tasks completed this week:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Created a plugin for Person Schema type</li>\r\n<li>Added option for Allowed/Forbidden context in all plugins</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, 1521, 1, 7190, '2022-11-07 11:04:23', 0, '2022-11-24 10:05:35', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1836, 0, 177, 'GSOC 2022 - Schema.org | Week 22', 'gsoc-2022-schema-org-week-22', '<p><strong>Date:</strong> 14th November – 20th November</p>\r\n<p>Hi, this is the progress report for the Schema.org project which is currently part of GSoC 2022.</p>\r\n<p>Tasks completed this week:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fixed Service Interface to show schema form only in the supported contexts</li>\r\n<li>Schema preview shown only for the schema types that are allowed in the context</li>\r\n<li>Created a subform for generic fields</li>\r\n<li>Added Organization Schema type</li>\r\n</ul>', NULL, 1, 1522, 1, 7190, '2022-11-21 12:23:29', 0, '2022-11-24 10:24:30', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1837, 0, 179, 'JXT Meeting Minutes - Nov 2 2022', 'jxt-nov-2-22', '<p dir="ltr"><strong>Scheduled duration:</strong> 90min</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Duration: </strong>120min</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>In Attendance:&nbsp;</strong>Crystal Dionysopoulos&nbsp;(Team Lead), Peter Martin (Assistant Team Lead), Angie Radke, Mark Fleeson, Benjamin Trenkle, Harald Leithner (5.0 Release manager), Olivier Buisard (4.3 release manager)</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>Absent:</strong> Milosz Wojaczek, Elisa Foltyn, Niels Braczek (Architecture Liaison), Shirielle Williams (4.3 Release manager), Robert Deutz (CMS Maintenance Liaison)</p>\r\n<h2>Topics:</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Team goals and tasks — prioritizing tasks, long term goals<ol>\r\n<li>Q4 goals in good shape - 50% done, 50% in progress</li>\r\n<li>Team requested more direct assignment of tasks and priorities from Crystal</li>\r\n<li>High collaboration needed between other teams in Joomla on projects</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li>JXT sprint?<ol>\r\n<li>Possibly next year in the spring</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n<li>New JED - need additional support for design and accessibility</li>\r\n<li>Joomla.org (and other sites) update<ol>\r\n<li>Will be done in working group/sub team of JXT</li>\r\n<li>First step: strategy for subdomains and site map; streamline it all</li>\r\n<li>Additional questions shared by Harald, copied into issue in team github repository</li>\r\n</ol></li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 1523, 1, 446, '2022-11-04 08:45:38', 0, '2022-11-25 08:50:34', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1838, 0, 179, 'JXT Meeting Minutes - Nov 23 2022', 'jxt-nov-23-22', '<p><strong>Scheduled duration:</strong> 60min</p>\r\n<p><strong>Duration</strong>: 60min</p>\r\n<p><strong>Participants</strong>:&nbsp;Crystal Dionysopoulos&nbsp;(Team Lead), Peter Martin (Assistant Team Lead), Angie Radke,&nbsp;Jarron White,&nbsp;Yuusuf Oladipo,&nbsp;Benjamin Trenkle&nbsp;(PLT Liaison),&nbsp;Niels Braczek (Architecture Liaison),&nbsp;Shirielle Williams(4.3 Release manager)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Absent</strong>:&nbsp;Elisa Foltyn,&nbsp;Milosz Wojaczek,&nbsp;Mark Fleeson,&nbsp;Robert Deutz (CMS Maintenance Liaison),&nbsp;Harald Leithner (Operations Liaison),&nbsp;Olivier Buisard (4.3 release manager)</p>\r\n<h2>Topics</h2>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Welcome Jarron and Yuusuf to the team!!</li>\r\n<li>Three projects right now:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>JWEB<br />redesign + restructure <a href="https://www.joomla.org/">https://www.joomla.org/</a></li>\r\n<li>JED4<br />The new Joomla Extension Directory (current one: https://extensions.joomla.org/ )</li>\r\n<li>J5UX<br />Improve UX in Joomla CMS itself (v4 and future v5)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Who wants to work on what?\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>JWEB:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Peter</li>\r\n<li>Angie</li>\r\n<li>Jarron</li>\r\n<li>Will take an agile approach to doing new structure and design on a backup of the live site</li>\r\n<li>Peter will ask Harald for a backup</li>\r\n<li>Crystal will ask Phil for who wants to be on the project from Marketing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>JED4: TBD - will discuss in channel</li>\r\n<li>J5UX: TBD - will discuss in channel</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>Will set an ongoing date for team meetings in order to make scheduling easier</li>\r\n</ol>', NULL, 1, 1524, 1, 446, '2022-11-25 08:50:45', 0, '2022-11-25 08:56:27', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1839, 0, 51, 'CMS Release Team Meeting November 09, 2022', 'cms-release-team-meeting-november-09-2022', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-d354ab91-7fff-7ee7-2c85-6f45ceb707e4" dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt;"><span style="font-size: 24.999999999999996pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">CMS Release Team Meeting 2022-11-09</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Wed, Nov, 09, 2022, UTC 18:00</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 14pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">DETAILS</span><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"><br /></span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Duration:&nbsp; 60 Minutes</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 14pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 13pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-a