n-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-inline-start: 48px;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;" role="presentation"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Joomla 4.2.4 security release was not successful in terms of releasing it, the version itself did not present any issues</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;" role="presentation"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Joomla 4.2.5 released successfully</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2 dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 18pt; margin-bottom: 6pt;"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Release 4.3</span></h2>\r\n<ul style="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-inline-start: 48px;">\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;" role="presentation"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Module versioning is removed from release. It needs to be better integrated.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;" role="presentation"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Issues with the accessibility plugin. It needs help with Typescript.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="list-style-type: disc; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre;" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;" role="presentation"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Question about documenting user help.</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 12pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Next CMS Release team meeting is scheduled for Wed. Nov 30, 18:00 UTC&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 1525, 1, 1036, '2022-11-30 12:48:22', 0, '2022-11-30 12:48:47', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1840, 0, 4, 'JCM Meeting Report - November 30th, 2022', 'jcm-meeting-report-november-30th-2022', '<p><strong>Attendees:</strong>&nbsp; Luca Marzo, Phil Walton, Anja de Crom, Hans van der Meer</p>\r\n<h3>What did we talk about</h3>\r\n<p><strong>November issue:</strong> a big thank you for everyone who contributed. This was a succesful issue!</p>\r\n<p><strong>December issue:</strong> since this was our monthly kickoff meeting, we\'ve discussed article ideas and things people are working on. Conclusion: the December issue may very well be just as interesting as the one from November. We\'ve added all ideas to the issue plan and asked a few authors if they think they\'ll be ready on time. For now, everything looks promising.</p>\r\n<p>The meeting lasted about 45 minutes.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 1526, 1, 6739, '2022-11-30 14:51:29', 0, '2022-11-30 14:55:15', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
