	(1842, 51, 0, 'Production Dept. Meeting MINUTES - November 29, 2022', 'production-dept-meeting-minutes-november-29-2022', '<h1 style="text-align: right;">Production Dept. Meeting MINUTES <br />- November&nbsp; 29, 2022</h1>\r\n<p><strong>Participants:</strong> Benjamin Trenkle (Department Coordinator), Hannes Papenberg (Team Leader), Harald Leithner (Release Lead 5.0), Mike Brandner (Team Leader), Olivier Buisard (Release Manager 4.3), Shirielle “SD” Williams (Release Manager 4.3), Roland Dalmulder (Release Lead 4.2), Franciska Perisa (Release Lead 4.2), Christiane Maier-Stadtherr (Team Leader), Viviana Menzel (Assistant Team Leader), Crystal Dionysopoulos (Team Leader), Jacob Waisner (Team Leader), Niels Braczek (Team Leader), Sigrid Gramlinger (Team Leader), Shivam Rajput (Team Leader), Philip Walton (Marketing Liaison), Robert Deutz (Team Leader), Tobias Zulauf (Release Lead 3.10) <br /> <strong>Absent:</strong> Llewellyn van der Merwe (Assistant Department Coordinator), David Jardin (Team Leader)</p>\r\n<h3><a href="/departments/production">Production Department</a> Coordinator (Benjamin Trenkle)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Congratulations to the first 4.3 Alpha 1 release</li>\r\n<li>To keep the meetings short, better separation of “Talk Topics” and “Updates/Proposed Topics”</li>\r\n<li>Motion will be send out:<br /> Handling the conversion of issues to discussions<br /> Since before there was no rule about the handling of the issues to discussion conversion, this motion sets the following rules:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>in general issues will not be converted to discussions</li>\r\n<li>if an issue appears to be a discussion only, the JBS team can decide (in an informal simple majority vote) to convert an issue to a discussion.</li>\r\n<li>other issues are either valid issues and should remain open until solved or addressed, or invalid/irrelevant issues which should be closed and possibly locked, with a note explaining why.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Joomla! <a href="/teams/joomla-enhancement-development-team">Enhancement Development</a> Team (Shivam Rajput)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Google Summer of Code (GSoC)\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>All student successfully passed the evaluation for Gsoc 2022.</li>\r\n<li>Planning underway for the Gsoc 2023</li>\r\n<li>Student already reaching out via emails and Twitter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Joomla! <a href="/teams/accessibility-team">Accessibility</a> Team (Christiane Maier-Stadtherr)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>New member - Alexa is joining the team as a technical writer to help with accessibility documentation!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Joomla! <a href="/teams/joomla-experience-team">Experience</a> Team (Crystal Dionysopoulos)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>PLT Strategy Sprint - reviewing possible dates, what to expect, and attendees.</li>\r\n<li>New JXT member! We’re happy to welcome Jarron as another UX Writer.</li>\r\n<li>The JXT is forming subgroups to work on three critical projects at the same time:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>JWEB - Joomla.org website strategy and template</li>\r\n<li>JED4 - the new Joomla Extensions Directory component</li>\r\n<li>J5UX - usability polishing and refinements for Joomla 5</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease let me know if anyone from your team would like to be involved in the subgroups. Thank you!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/security-strike-team">Security Strike</a> Team (David Jardin)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>We are planning to implement an secret repo to manage our CVEs via Pull Requests implementing the cve-cna-bot gh action: <br /><a href="https://github.com/marketplace/actions/cve-cna-bot">https://github.com/marketplace/actions/cve-cna-bot</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/cms-release-team">CMS Release</a> Team (Sigrid Gramlinger)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Internal documentation on building releases was updated/restructured by Harald and also integrated from Docs by Franciska. Thanks!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/cms-maintenance-team">CMS Maintenance</a> Team (Robert Deutz)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Joomla Translations: Crowdin is currently on J4.2, we cannot have two versions at the same time. Stefan needs support for planning and ideas, how and when to support 4.3 and later 5.<br /> One option: decision to change from 4.2 to 4.3 when 4.3 is in beta phase. We will discuss this in our next team meeting.<br /> But what shall we do with J5?<br /> =&gt; Niels, Harald and Stefan to find a solution for Joomla 5.<br /> =&gt; Sigrid will create a profile board on Mattermost for new supporters</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Release Managers (Harald, Niels, Olivier, SD, Roland, Franciska, Tobias, Llewellyn)</h3>\r\n<h4>Release Lead 4.3 (Olivier Buisard, Shirielle “SD” Williams):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Alpha 1 Release Today</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Release Lead 4.2 (Roland Dalmulder, Franciska Perisa):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>4.2.6 RC is coming this weekend</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><a href="/teams/software-architecture-strategy-working-group">Software Architecture &amp; Strategy</a> Team (Niels Braczek)</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Crystal joined the team as a liaison from JXT. We see common objectives from different perspectives.</li>\r\n<li>Talked about possible ways to make the RFC process more attractive resp. approachable.</li>\r\n<li>Reached out for additional team members.</li>\r\n<li>Motions end tomorrow</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3>Other Business</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>How should we handle the further development of the Search component<br /> =&gt; Motions are being created to define the EOL and the kind of support we will provide<br /> =&gt; Olivier &amp; Phil writing an Magazine article about migration to Smart Search<br /> =&gt; Needs documentation<br /> =&gt; Post-Installation Message for 4.3 about the decision &amp; what it means for site admins</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>', NULL, 1, 1528, 6, 1755, '2022-12-07 09:55:00', 1755, '2022-12-09 04:37:27', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1843, 58, 0, 'OSM, Inc. - Full Board Meeting - November 03, 2022', 'osm-inc-full-board-meeting-november-03-2022', '<h2 dir="ltr">Open Source Matters, Inc.<br />Full Board of Directors and Officers Meeting</h2>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Date: November 03, 2022<br />Time: 18:00 UTC<br />Total time of meeting: 1 hour 35 minutes</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Attendees:</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Robert Deutz (President), Nicola Galgano (Vice President), Luca Marzo (Secretary), Nadja Lamisch (Treasurer), Benjamin Trenkle (Director), Philip Walton (Director), Harald Leithner (Director).</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Apologies:</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Proxies:</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-</p>\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">Discussion outline</h2>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Treasurer</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Nadja obtained her passport, so that she can start to organize the trip to NY for the bank.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">GSoC informed that the payment will be made once the projects have been completed, at the end of November.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Nadja and Robert worked with Karen on the books.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Production Department</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Joomla 4.2.4 successfully released.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Starting with 4.3 release preparation.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Successful CMS Maintainer sprint in Munich.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Outreach Department</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Joomla 4.2.4 marketing released and newsletter, new volunteer to help with Newsletters being trained</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Document Buddies launched, article written for magazine and group formed in glip with more being added.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Operations Department</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Mattermost is ready to go</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">We need a launch date, and a plan for transition</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">It’s not possible to transfer old Chats to Mattermost</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">It’s not possible to export old chats from Glip (it seems we don’t have the permissions on any account, Glip support wasn’t able to help)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">We should advertise on all Glip Channel including that Glip will be closed and deleted in a certain number of months. This notification should be sent in each channel every week.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Semi annual meetings should be possible on Mattermost since public beta for voice chat on the cloud instance is limited to 200 people now.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">JXT starts with the basic concept on joomla.org (template/structure/needs).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Mark Fleeson is new Team Lead on JED.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Q3 Quarterly report published.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Vice President</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Nicola reminded the need to arrange a Semi-Annual Meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Nicola requested updates on outstanding legal cases.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Secretary</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>Reporting</strong>] Quarterly reports from Board Members were due on October 04 (Group 2) and October 12 (Group 1).</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>Deadlines</strong>] On October 14, 2022 were due:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Annual Filing for Charitable organizations (New York State) - CHAR500</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">US Corporation Income Tax - Form 1120.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Deadlines were extended by Danielle who worked on the filings already.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>AdSense</strong>] Latest payment from Google AdSense has been processed on September 21, 2022 for USD 921,37. Revenues from AdSense are almost stable at about 900 USD per month. Invalid traffic has decreased over the last months. It’s opportune to evaluate the new option offered by AdSense to serve first-party cookies, to check whether this could lead to increased ad revenues.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>Analytics</strong>] Since Google will sunset Google Analytics 3 (Universal Analytics) in July 2023, it’s opportune to start planning a migration path to Google Analytics 4 on time. Also, we need to ensure that the configuration of Analytics doesn’t store/process personal data.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>GitHub Sponsors</strong>] Through GitHub Sponsors it’s now possible to receive custom amounts as sponsorship, starting from 5 USD that is the minimum threshold.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>Correspondence</strong>] We received an invoice from PRNewsWire in our PO Box.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>Income</strong>] It’s crucial to revitalize the Capital Team. The previous attempt evidently failed due to unavailability of members. In order to avoid the need to rebudget, we need to re-establish the operation of the Capital Team. Refer to <a href="https://github.com/open-source-matters/contact-us/discussions/4">Capital Team Restart · Discussion #4 · open-source-matters/contact-us · GitHub</a>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">[<strong>Harbor Compliance</strong>] Harbord Compliance service expired, even though we approved the expenses months ago. Robert is dealing with the renewal.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">President</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Robert shared with the Board a request from some extension developers to act as an umbrella organization for the fork of an extension. Robert to answer them.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Robert worked on legal stuff.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Robert worked with Nadja on getting her up to speed as treasurer.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Robert had meetings with Karen and Nadja to work on the books.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Other Business</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Benjamin proposed to organize event visits and create visibility for Joomla or give education benefits for team leads (e.g. <a href="https://23.foss-backstage.de/">https://23.foss-backstage.de/</a>)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Motions taken during this meeting</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/072 - The Secretary proposes to adjourn the meeting.<br /></strong>Proposed by Luca Marzo, seconded by Benjamin Trenkle.<br /><em>The motion passed with unanimous consent.</em></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Motions taken offline before this meeting</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/070 - Approve and publish the Board Meeting Minutes.<br /></strong>Proposed by Luca Marzo, seconded by Nicola Galgano.<br /><em>The motion passed with unanimous consent.&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/071 - Move meeting time to 18.00 UTC to reflect timeshift in Europe<br /></strong>Proposed by Luca Marzo, seconded by Robert Deutz.<br /><em>The motion passed with unanimous consent.&nbsp;</em></p>', NULL, 1, 1529, 1, 669, '2022-12-11 15:18:17', 0, '2022-12-11 15:20:10', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1844, 58, 0, 'OSM, Inc. - Full Board Meeting - December 01, 2022', 'osm-inc-full-board-meeting-december-01-2022', '<h2 dir="ltr">Open Source Matters, Inc.<br />Full Board of Directors and Officers Meeting</h2>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Date: December 01, 2022<br />Time: 18:00 UTC<br />Total time of meeting: 1 hour 35 minutes</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Attendees:</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">Robert Deutz (President), Nicola Galgano (Vice President), Luca Marzo (Secretary), Nadja Lamisch (Treasurer), Benjamin Trenkle (Director), Philip Walton (Director), Harald Leithner (Director).</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Apologies:</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-</p>\r\n<h4 dir="ltr">Proxies:</h4>\r\n<p dir="ltr">-</p>\r\n<h2 dir="ltr">Discussion outline</h2>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Treasurer</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">The Board discussed the current bank situation and the related difficulties with accessing accounts.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">The Board is exploring the opportunity to move to another bank.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Nadja needs to travel to New York and meet Danielle to solve banking issues.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Robert and Nadja worked on the list of active sponsor contracts.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Production Department</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Joomla! 4.2.5 successfully released.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Joomla! 4.3.0 Alpha 1 successfully released.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">GSoC 22 done, starting with 2023 preparation.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">New members are joining the Accessibility Team and the Experience Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Outreach Department</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Joomla! 4.2.5 marketing posted including the newsletter.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Joomla! 4.3.0 Alpha 1 marketing posted.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">November Issue of the magazine published and December in production.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Article on using Mattermost to help migration with 271 active members not on board.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Philip shared an opportunity to partner with a gamification service, thanks to the lead created by Brian Teeman.&nbsp;</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">The Outreach Department is working on new options for sponsors to support the project.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Operations Department</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Issues related to the Launch platform have been increasing recently.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">JXT started working on the new website design and concept.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">A DDoS attack to another client on our hosting provider caused degraded performance to our web properties. The attack has been successfully mitigated by the provider.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Still no plans to update our websites to Joomla 4.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Forum received a DDoS attack yesterday, mitigated by the hosting provider. The Team is evaluating the adoption of Cloudflare to increase the protection of the forum.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Mastodon instance is running but is waiting for SAML integration with identity.joomla.org</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">We should get an entry in the DMCA Designated Agent Directory in case someone wants to file a DMCA takedown notice against any of our properties.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">SSO for several Joomla properties is planned, likely joomla.org and developer.joomla.org is next.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Updates for documentation manual.joomla.org and internal.joomla.org are done semi automatic with Docusaurus and will be changed to fully automatically if no unexpected problems occur in the next couple of months.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Team census</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Capital Team has 2 active members but no Team Lead (for personal reasons), there is an ongoing discussion in the Board to restart this team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">The Extensions Directory Team has 6 active members.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Forum Team has 5 active members.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Trademark &amp; Licensing Team has 2 active members (We need at least 1 more)</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Showcase Directory Team 4 active members. Team is planned to be merged into the Community Site Team.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Volunteers Portal Team Only one member left, Sander finally stepped down today. Team is planned to be merged into Community Site Team</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">The Privacy Compliance Team is not active. Discussion about moving the needed tasks to the board (Privacy complaints), ending the GDPR (and other DP LAWs) advice task.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="2">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Webmasters Working Group, collection of members most of them will be part of the community sites team. Working Group is planned to be merged into Community Site Team</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Vice President</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Nicola proposed to participate at FOSDEM 2023, sending close representatives.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Nicola requested to choose the date for the Semi-Annual Members Meeting.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Secretary</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Luca shared some outstanding invoices from Veem and Cision received in the PO Box. The Treasurer is already working on that.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">President</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Next Term as President: I am not planning to run for president the next time. I just want to give early notice.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Working on getting Sponsors List up to date.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">No news on outstanding legal cases.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Other business</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" aria-level="1">\r\n<p dir="ltr" role="presentation">Semi-Annual Members Meeting is planned for December 15, 2022 at 18.00 UTC.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Motions taken during this meeting</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/075 - Disband the Volunteers Portal Team.<br /></strong>Proposed by Harald Leithner, seconded by Robert Deutz.<br /><em>The motion passed with unanimous consent.</em></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/076 - Disband the Showcase Directory Team.<br /></strong>Proposed by Harald Leithner, seconded by Robert Deutz.<br /><em>The motion passed with unanimous consent.</em></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/077 - Promote the Community Sites Team from a Working Group to a Team with Voting rights.<br /></strong>Proposed by Harald Leither, seconded by Robert Deutz.<br /><em>The motion passed with majority consent and 1 vote against. Nicola Galgano voted against.</em></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/078 - Disband the Privacy Compliance Team and move the responsibility to the Board.<br /></strong>Proposed by Harald Leithner, seconded by Luca Marzo<br /><em>The motion passed with unanimous content.</em></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/079 - The Secretary proposes to adjourn the meeting.<br /></strong>Proposed by Luca Marzo, seconded by Benjamin Trenkle.<br /><em>The motion passed with majority consent and 1 vote against. Nicola Galgano voted against.</em></p>\r\n<h3 dir="ltr">Motions taken offline before this meeting</h3>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/074 - The Board approves an official Mastodon instance for the Joomla Community<br /></strong>Proposed by Harald Leithner, seconded by Luca Marzo.<br />The motion passed with unanimous consent.</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr"><strong>#2022/073 - Approve and publish the Board Meeting Minutes.<br /></strong>Proposed by Luca Marzo, seconded by Robert Deutz.<br /><em>The motion passed with unanimous consent.&nbsp;</em></p>', NULL, 1, 1530, 1, 669, '2022-12-11 15:20:27', 0, '2022-12-11 15:23:28', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
	(1845, 0, 25, 'Joomla Bug Squad Meeting - December 2, 2022 ', 'joomla-bug-squad-meeting-december-2-2022', '<p id="docs-internal-guid-44f41d48-7fff-c8ee-3200-476b8ad58bfa" dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Date: December 2, 2022</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Time: 21:00 UTC</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Total time of meeting: 1 Hour</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Attendees: Richard Fath, Nicola Galgono</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">, Martin Kopp, Jacob Waisner</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 16pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Current status</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;"> In the last 30 days:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">693 Issues remain open</span></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;168 Issues Closed</span></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;224 PRs remain open</span></li>\r\n<li dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">&nbsp;69 PRs merged</span><