	(1851, 0, 5, 'Events Team Meeting December 16, 2022', 'events-team-meeting-december-16-2022', '<p dir="ltr"><strong>Present:</strong> SD, Lou Hawkins (LH), Viviana Menzel (VM), Todd Woodward (TW) and Patrick Jackson (PJ)<br /><strong>Apologies:</strong> Phillip Walton&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Mattermost</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: SD asked if all team members were on Mattermost.&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">In the transition from Glip to Mattermost, all links and leads have been captured; however, SD will do a final check before losing access to Glip.</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">An Events Team board has been created to track tasks.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="caret-color: #000000; color: #000000;"><span id="docs-internal-guid-a71f5b2a-7fff-1b53-a021-64eefb7cafd3"></span><br class="Apple-interchange-newline" /></span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Publishing Notifications and Events:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">LH said marketing could help liaise with the social media team for promotion.<br /><br /></span></p>\r\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-3f4855fd-7fff-94ba-f268-2676ae2cc5c6" style="caret-color: #000000; color: #000000;"></span><span id="docs-internal-guid-986c8c61-7fff-8a46-4064-17dc0aba0e64" style="caret-color: #000000; color: #000000;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-weight: bold; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">TASK</span><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">: How can the events team help? What can we do that we haven’t done previously? What can we do better? </span></span><br class="Apple-interchange-newline" style="caret-color: #000000; color: #000000;" /></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: bold; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">Feedback Task:</span></p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">What should the events team look like in 2023? What should we be doing? It must be made clear that we don’t organize events, but we will assist every step of the way with Tip Sheets, Links on how to request funds etc... Send any ideas by email to SD or post on Mattermost.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p dir="ltr" style="line-height: 1.38; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Arial; color: #000000; background-color: transparent; font-weight: 400; font-style: normal; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-position: normal; text-decoration: none; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;">The next Meeting is scheduled for January 20th 2023, at 7am (Chicago Time) or 1pm UTC.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style="caret-color: #000000; color: #000000;"></span><br class="Apple-interchange-newline" style="caret-color: #000000; color: #000000;" /></p>', NULL, 1, 1537, 1, 3274, '2022-12-20 11:00:00', 0, '2022-12-31 22:45:54', 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00');
